Q7: What is the difference between TCG and KVM?

<details>
<summary><b>Answer</b></summary>

Feature TCG KVM
Type Software emulator Hardware virtualization
Performance Slow (10-100x slower) Fast (near-native)
Architecture Any guest on any host Guest must match host
Memory Software MMU Hardware EPT/NPT
CPU Interpret/translate Native execution
Devices Software emulated Software emulated
Latency High (100μs+) Low (10μs)
Use case Development, testing Production, cloud

TCG (Tiny Code Generator):

· Translates guest code to TCG IR, then to host code
· Example: Run ARM binaries on x86
· No hardware support needed

KVM (Kernel-based Virtual Machine):

· Uses CPU hardware virtualization (VT-x, AMD-V)
· Example: Run x86 VMs on x86 hosts
· Needs hardware support

In QEMU:

· -accel tcg = software emulation
· -accel kvm = hardware virtualization
· Can mix: TCG for some CPUs, KVM for others (rare)

</details>

Q8: How does QEMU handle interrupts?

