Section 4.1: QEMU with CXL (Compute Express Link)

CXL Architecture in QEMU

What is CXL?

· Cache-coherent interconnect for memory expansion
· 32 GT/s (Gen 2), 64 GT/s (Gen 3)
· Sub-microsecond latency
· Memory pooling across hosts

QEMU CXL Implementation:

```c
// hw/cxl/cxl-device-utils.c

// CXL Type 3 (memory) device
typedef struct CXLType3Dev {
    PCIDevice parent;
    MemoryRegion device_memory;
    MemoryRegion volatile_mem;
    MemoryRegion persistent_mem;
    uint64_t mem_size;
    uint64_t pmem_size;
    bool volatile_memory;
    bool persistent_memory;
} CXLType3Dev;

// CXL device initialization
static void cxl_type3_realize(PCIDevice *dev, Error **errp) {
    CXLType3Dev *ct3d = CXL_TYPE3(dev);
    
    // 1. Initialize CXL capability
    cxl_device_init(dev, &ct3d->cxl_cap);
    
    // 2. Allocate memory
